---
description: Project code conventions (single source of truth)
alwaysApply: true
---

Follow the conventions in `AGENTS.md` at the repository root — it is the single
source of truth for architecture, layering, and code patterns in this repo.

Highest-impact rules (full detail in AGENTS.md):

- Persistence and storage side-effects go in the **server action**, never in a
  client zod `.transform()`.
- `'use server'` only on RPC entry points called from the client; internal server
  helpers are plain modules.
- New domain logic follows `server/<domain>/{actions,queries,schemas}.ts`; copy
  `server/barometers/` as the template.
- Client code never lives under `server/`.
- `bun run lint && bun run typecheck && bun run jest` must pass before committing.
